Joseph Olaoluwa The Lagos State Government has announced a change in the dates for the closure of the rail level crossing on Ilupeju, Ogunmokun, Jibowu and Yaba for construction works. It said the new closure dates for construction work to be undertaken would now be Monday, November 16 for Ilupeju; Tuesday 17 for Ogunmokun; while Jibowu and Yaba would be closed Wednesday, November 18. It added that the time remained 8pm to 7am. This is according to a statement received on Sunday from the Ministry of Transportation which referenced a slight adjustment in closure dates for the rail level crossing. Prior to the adjustment, the ministry had planned to close the rail level crossing on Ilupeju on Sunday 15th, Ogunmokun on Monday 16th, Jibowu, and Yaba on Wednesday 18th of November, 2020 for construction works. Copyright PUNCH.
